<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="165" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="165">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="165">
Total body length ranged within 6.1 and 6.7 mm. Tail 30.5-31.7% of body length. Hooks 6. Anterior teeth 3-4 and posterior teeth 5-6, respectively. Rigid and opaque body (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. A Aidanosagitta regularis (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: CC = corona ciliata; COL = collarette; E = eye; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704204" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">20</figureCitation>
). Head small, triangular shaped (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. A Aidanosagitta regularis (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: CC = corona ciliata; COL = collarette; E = eye; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704204" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">20B</figureCitation>
). Round eyes with 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“B”">&quot;B&quot;</normalizedToken>
-shaped eye pigments (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. A Aidanosagitta regularis (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: CC = corona ciliata; COL = collarette; E = eye; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704204" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">20B</figureCitation>
). Collarette expanding to seminal vesicles (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. A Aidanosagitta regularis (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: CC = corona ciliata; COL = collarette; E = eye; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704204" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">20A</figureCitation>
). Corona ciliata beginning from neck to anterior of ventral ganglion (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Position and shape of corona ciliata A Aidanosagitta regularis B Pterosagitta draco C Serratosagitta pacifica D Flaccisagitta enflata." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704194" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">10A</figureCitation>
). Anterior fins 12.3% of body length. Anterior fins beginning at posterior of ventral ganglion. Starting points of anterior fins 37.3% and ending points of anterior fins 50.9% of body length, respectively (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. A Aidanosagitta regularis (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: CC = corona ciliata; COL = collarette; E = eye; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704204" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">20D</figureCitation>
). Posterior fins 22.0% of body length and 1.8 times longer than anterior fins. Starting points of posterior fins 62.9% and ending points of posterior fins 84.7% of body length, respectively. Posterior fins not connected to anterior fins, beginning in front of caudal septum and both anterior fins and posterior fins completely rayed (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. A Aidanosagitta regularis (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: CC = corona ciliata; COL = collarette; E = eye; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704204" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">20D, E</figureCitation>
). Caudal fin fully rayed and roughly round or triangle-shaped (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. A Aidanosagitta regularis (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: CC = corona ciliata; COL = collarette; E = eye; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704204" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">20C</figureCitation>
). Intestinal diverticula present (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Intestinal diverticular (shown by white arrow) A Aidanosagitta regularis (present) B Ferosagitta robusta (present) C Zonosagitta nagae (absent) D Zonosagitta bedoti (absent)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704191" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">7A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. A Aidanosagitta regularis (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: CC = corona ciliata; COL = collarette; E = eye; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704204" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">20B</figureCitation>
). Seminal vesicles longitudinally elongated along body (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. A Aidanosagitta regularis (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: CC = corona ciliata; COL = collarette; E = eye; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704204" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">20C</figureCitation>
). Eggs reaching posterior of ventral ganglion.
</paragraph>
